word_group.brief_definition: 捕食者和猎物；捕食者及其猎物；天敌和猎物

bilingual.source: Predators as well as prey were welcome in their backyard.
bilingual.target: 捕食者和猎物都欢迎来到他们的后院。

bilingual.source: The lion hunts for its prey at night.
The feline predator stalked its prey silently.
bilingual.target: 这只猫科的捕食者悄悄地跟踪猎物。

bilingual.source: Some predators use camouflage to sneak up on their prey.
bilingual.target: 一些捕食者使用伪装来悄悄接近它们的猎物。

bilingual.source: Antelopes often fall prey to predators like lions and cheetahs.
bilingual.target: 羚羊经常成为狮子和猎豹等捕食者的猎物。

bilingual.source: Researchers use the Lotka-volterra equations to study predator-prey relationships.
bilingual.target: 研究人员使用洛特卡-沃尔泰拉模型方程来研究捕食者与猎物的关系。

bilingual.source: Kleptoplasty allows certain organisms to perform photosynthesis even after consuming their prey.
bilingual.target: 盗叶现象使某些生物在捕食后仍能进行光合作用。

bilingual.source: Predators often hunt at night to catch their prey off guard.
bilingual.target: 捕食者经常在夜间狩猎，以便出其不意地捕捉猎物。

bilingual.source: Birds of prey are considered predators because they hunt other animals.
bilingual.target: 猛禽被认为是捕食者，因为它们捕猎其他动物。

bilingual.source: Ciliophora play a crucial role in aquatic ecosystems as both predators and prey.
bilingual.target: 纤毛虫门在水生生态系统中作为捕食者和猎物起着至关重要的作用。

list.abstract: 《PREY》（掠食），由2Human Head Studios, Inc.和Venom Games开发的一款FPS类的游戏，于2006年7月11日由Sold Out Sales & Marketing Ltd.和Spike Co., Ltd.在PC、MAC、Xbox360、ZBO发行。 《PREY》讲述了一位名为汤米的切诺基人，为了拯救被外星人绑架的女友以及祖父，也为了拯救地球，义无反顾的踏上了危机四伏的外星飞船。在宇宙船中，处处都潜伏着危机，玩家在探索的过程中除了要对付各种各样的敌人外，还有大量的解谜装置。 游戏将对应Xbox Live提供最多8人的在线对战，分死亡竞赛和团队死亡竞赛两种模式。玩家可以在墙壁上行走，可以通过天花板靠近敌人发动奇袭，敌人会寻找对自己有利的位置射击，会研究玩家的战术，找到软肋进行攻击。
prey是一个英语单词，意思是猎物。

yingyinNormal.en: But for how long? Prey and predators are so close.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但是能藏多久？捕食者和猎物如此接近。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, then, you're letting the water make you its prey.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这么说，你是水的猎物罗。

yingyinNormal.en: The Golden Eagle, one of the world's most effective birds of prey.
yingyinNormal.zh: 金雕是世界上最有力的猛禽之一。

yingyinNormal.en: Back then, the world was divided in two. Vicious predator, or meek prey.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那时世界分成两部分，凶残的食肉动物，和温顺的食草动物。

yingyinNormal.en: And for a tiger, it's like crawling on your belly to stalk helpless prey.
yingyinNormal.zh: 对老虎来说，就像匍匐前进，悄悄接近无辜的猎物。

yingyinNormal.en: Trust me, Kripke will fall easy prey to my psychological warfare. Observe.
yingyinNormal.zh: 信我，克里帕奇很快就会倒在我的心理战上的，观察吧。

yingyinNormal.en: But faster, OK? Now, claw, kick, claw, kick. I'm stalking the prey. Claw, kick.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但速度要快一点，像这样，划、踢，划、踢 匍匐前进，划、踢。

yingyinNormal.en: I wonder why? Jealousy, mostly. But the point is that fear is natural. Fear is for prey.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我很好奇为什么呢? 主要是因为嫉妒 回到重点，恐惧是天性 猎物才有恐惧。

yingyinNormal.en: So that's it? Prey fears predator, and you stay in power? Yeah. Pretty much. It won't work.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你的目的就是这个吗？食草动物畏惧食肉动物，然后你掌权？差不多吧。不会得逞的。

yingyinNormal.en: Now predator and prey live in harmony. And every young mammal has multitudinous opportunities.
yingyinNormal.zh: 现在食肉和食草动物和谐共处，每只哺乳动物的未来都有了无限可能。

yingyinNormal.en: Colonel Forster is a sensible man. He will keep her out of any real mischief. And she's far too poor to be an object of prey to anyone.
yingyinNormal.zh: 费斯托上校是个有见识的人，他不会让她闯出什么祸事来的。她太穷，谁也不会看中她。

yingyinNormal.en: Fear, treachery, blood lust. Thousands of years ago, these were the forces that ruled our world. A world where prey were scared of predators.
yingyinNormal.zh: 恐惧，背叛和嗜血，数万年前支配着我们的世界，那时食草动物惧怕食肉动物。

yingyinNormal.en: Hello, Amy Farrah Fowler. I'm sorry to inform you that you have been taken in by unsupportable mathematics designed to prey on the gullible and the lonely.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你好，艾米·菲拉·福勒，我很遗憾地告诉你，你上当了，被设计用来欺骗很傻很天真剩男剩女的无知算法骗了。

yingyinNormal.en: Naive little hick with good grades and big ideas decides "Hey, look at me, I'm gonna move to Zootopia, where predators and prey live in harmony and sing Kumbaya!"
yingyinNormal.zh: 天真的小山妞成绩好有理想就觉得我得去动物城，食肉和食草动物和平相处，还一起唱山歌。

examination_example.sentence: As such, different populations of killer whales have had to learn different hunting techniques in order to gain the upper hand over their local <highlight>prey</highlight> (猎物) .

examination_example.sentence: According to a newly published study, cats seem to be able to predict the location of hiding <highlight>prey</highlight> (猎物) using both their ears and an inborn (天生的) understanding of how the physical world works.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 根据一项最新发表的研究，猫咪似乎能够利用它们的耳朵和对物理世界运作的天生理解来预测隐藏的猎物的位置。

examination_example.sentence: The researchers conclude that cats hunting style may have developed based on their common-sense abilities to infer where <highlight>prey</highlight> is, using their hearing.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 研究人员得出结论，猫咪的狩猎方式可能是基于它们的常识能力而发展的，这种能力是利用它们的听力来推断猎物在哪里的。
